{{Infobox language |name=Eperara |nativename=Epena |altname=Saija |states=[[Colombia]] |speakers=3,552 in Colombia and Ecuador |date=2004–2011 |ref=<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/sja|title=Epena|work=Ethnologue|access-date=2018-07-23|language=en}}</ref> |speakers2=plus an unknown number in Panama<ref name=e18>{{Ethnologue18|sja}}</ref> |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Chocoan languages|Chocoan]] |fam2=[[Emberá languages|Emberá]] |fam3=Southern |iso3=sja |glotto=epen1239 |glottorefname=Epena }}
'''Eperara''' {{aka}} '''Epena''' (Southern Embera) is an [[Embera language]] of Colombia, with about 250 speakers in Ecuador.
