{{Infobox person | name = Max Lundgren | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1937|3|22|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Landskrona]], Sweden | death_date = {{Death date and age|2005|5|27|1937|3|22|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Malmö]], Sweden | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = [[author]] }} '''Max Lundgren''' (22 March 1937 – 27 May 2005) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] author of children's books.<ref name=sfi /> He debuted in 1962 with the book ''[[Hunden som äntligen visslade]]'', and has since written a total of about 50 books.<ref name=dn /> Some of his books have become TV series, among other ''[[Pojken med guldbyxorna]]'' and his books about fictional Swedish soccer club ''[[Åshöjdens BK]]''.<ref name=dn />
