{{Infobox language |name=Mubi |states=[[Chad]] |region=central |speakers={{sigfig|35300|2}} |date=1993 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] |fam4=[[East Chadic B languages|East Chadic B]] |fam5=[[Mubi languages]] (B.1.2) |iso3=mub |glotto=mubi1246 |glottorefname=Mubi (Chad) }}
'''Mubi''' (also known as Moubi) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in central [[Chad]]. It forms one of the [[Mubi languages]], a group of [[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] languages.
