{{Use Indian English|date=June 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}} {{Orphan|date=November 2011}}
'''Shikharipura Harihareshwara''' ({{lang-kn|ಶಿಕಾರಿಪುರ ಹರಿಹರೇಶ್ವರ}}) (1936 – 23 July 2010) was a [[Kannada language|Kannada]] writer. He served as the chief editor of 'Amerikannada', a bimonthly magazine in Kannada. In 1999, he was among the recipients of the [[Rajyothsava award]] constituted by [[Government of Karnataka]]. He was widely known for the literary work he did residing in United States of America.
==Works== * 'Darshana' * Hariharēśvara, Es. Ke. Kannaḍa Uḷisi Beḷasuva Bage: "Amerikannaḍa"da Cintanegaḷu. Maisūru: Saṃvahana, 2005. Print. [http://lccn.loc.gov/2007343994 'US Library of Congress permalink']
==External links== * [https://web.archive.org/web/20121004205915/http://archive.deccanherald.com/content/Dec152007/district2007121541298.asp 'NRI Kannadigas not Refugees'] * [http://www.ourkarnataka.com/Articles/starofmysore/shikari09.htm Obituary on OurKarnataka.com] * [http://sjoshi.podbean.com/2010/07/24/tribute-to-late-sk-harihareshwara/ Obituary by writer Srivathsa Joshi] * Wikipedia page on Shikaripura Harihareshwara in Kannada language [[:kn:ಶಿಕಾರಿಪುರ ಹರಿಹರೇಶ್ವರ]]
