|}

* {{IPA|/m, p, β/}} are [[Bilabial consonant|bilabial]], whereas {{IPA|/w/}} is [[Labialized velar consonant|labialized velar]].
** {{IPA|/β/}} is most typically a fricative {{IPAblink|β}}, but other realizations (such as an approximant {{IPAblink|β̞}}, a stop {{IPAblink|b}} and an affricate {{IPAblink|bβ}}) also appear. The stop realization is most likely to appear in word-initial stressed syllables, whereas the approximant realization appears most often as onsets to non-initial unstressed syllables.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=282}}
* {{IPA|/n, ts, s/}} are alveolar {{IPA|[{{IPA link|n}}, {{IPA link|ts}}, {{IPA link|s}}]}}, whereas {{IPA|/t/}} is dental {{IPAblink|t̪}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=281}}
* The {{IPA|/ʂ–ʃ/}} distinction can be described as an apical–laminal one.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=282}}
* {{IPA|/tʃ, ʃ/}} are [[Palato-alveolar consonant|palato-alveolar]], whereas {{IPA|/j/}} is palatal.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=281}}
* Before nasal vowels, {{IPA|/w, j/}} are [[Nasalization|nasalized]] {{IPA|[{{IPA link|w̃}}, {{IPA link|j̃}}]}} and may be even realized close to nasal stops {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ŋ|ŋʷ}}, {{IPA link|ɲ}}]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=283}}
* {{IPA|/w/}} is realized as {{IPAblink|w}} before {{IPA|/a, ã/}}, as {{IPAblink|ɥ}} before {{IPA|/i, ĩ/}} and as {{IPAblink|ɰ}} before {{IPA|/ɯ, ɯ̃/}}. It does not occur before {{IPA|/o, õ/}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=283}}
* {{IPA|/ɻ/}} is a very variable sound:
** Intervocalically, it is realized either as an approximant {{IPAblink|ɻ}}, or sometimes as a (weak) fricative {{IPAblink|ʐ}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=282}}
** Sometimes (especially in the beginning of a stressed syllable) it can be realized as a postalveolar affricate {{IPA|[d̠͡z̠]}}, or a stop-appproximant sequence {{IPA|[d̠ɹ̠]}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=283}}
** It can also be realized as a postalveolar flap {{IPAblink|ɾ̠}}.{{sfnp|Valenzuela|Márquez Pinedo|Maddieson|2001|p=282}}

