{{Infobox language |name=Tindi |nativename=Идараб мицци ''Idarab mittsi'' |states=[[Russia]] |region=Southern [[Dagestan]] |speakers={{sigfig|2150|2}} |date=2010 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Caucasian |fam1=[[Northeast Caucasian languages|Northeast Caucasian]] |fam2=[[Avar–Andic languages|Avar–Andic]] |fam3=[[Andic languages|Andic]] |fam4=Akhvakh–Tindi |fam5=Karata–Tindi |fam6=Botlikh–Tindi |fam7=Bagvalal–Tindi |iso3=tin |glotto=tind1238 |glottorefname=Tindi }}
'''Tindi''' is an [[Northeast Caucasian languages|Northeast Caucasian language]] spoken in the [[Russia]]n republic of [[Dagestan]]. Tindis call their language ''Idarab mitstsi'' meaning 'the language of the Idar village'. It is only an oral language; [[Avar language|Avar]] or [[Russian language|Russian]] are used in written communication instead. It has approximately 2,150 speakers.<ref name="e18" />
